@marshallford You can use either one in a container depending on your use case. You can also increase/decrease the security you need.  

For building a container in a locked down container you would be better off with buildah. 

You could use `buildah bud --isolation chroot -f Dockerfile .`

@hulkish I've started to work on an image under my own org (for now). It is a bit heavy and has an old version of runc but feel free to take a look and/or submit a PR. Thanks.

https://hub.docker.com/r/marshallford/podman
